<h1>Dialogue boxes</h1>

<p class="intro">
    Use dialogue boxes to convey important information to the user.
</p>

<ol>
    <li><a href="#anchor1">Error dialogue</a></li>
    <li><a href="#anchor2">Information dialogue</a></li>
    <li><a href="#anchor3">Success dialogue</a></li>
    <li><a href="#anchor4">Warning dialogue</a></li>
</ol>

<h3 id="anchor1">1. Error dialogue</h3>

<p>
    Use the error dialogue to highlight problems to the user.
    This might be a problem with information they have provided or a problem with our systems that is preventing them from doing something.
</p>

<div class="tab-set">
    <%- partial('../../_partials/tabs', { id: 'error' }) %>
    <section>
        <div class="tab1 component-example">
            <%- partial('../../_partials/dialog', {
                dialogClass: 'error',
                dialogTitle: "There's a problem",
                dialogMessage: "It looks like there might be a problem with our system. Please try again in a few minutes. We’re sorry for the inconvenience."
            }) %>
        </div>
        <div class="tab2 component-html">
            HTML injected here
        </div>
        <div class="tab3 component-angular">
            <h5>Angular example usage:</h5>
            <script type="text/plain" class="language-html">
<app-dialogue title="There's a problem" type="error">
    <p>It looks like there might be a problem with our system. Please try again in a few minutes. We’re sorry for the inconvenience.</p>
</app-dialogue>
            </script>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>

